title: The profit and loss of Great-Britain and Spain : from the commencement of the present war, to this time, impartially stated : by laying before the publick, as perfect and regular a list, as can be hand, of all the ships taken from either nation, since the beginning of the war, to this time : with proper remarks upon the list of British ships, in a pamphlet, intitled, Hireling artifice detected : in a letter to the author
imprint: Printed for T. Cooper, at the Globe in Paternoster-Row
author: Philalethes
